e and easy! A great choice to get started with Bevy"},{"id":2747858849,"node_id":"MDU6TGFiZWwyNzQ3ODU4ODQ5","url":"https://api.github.com/repos/bevyengine/bevy/labels/A-Meta","name":"A-Meta","color":"c6a751","default":false,"description":"About the project itself"}],"state":"closed","locked":false,"assignee":null,"assignees":[],"milestone":null,"comments":0,"created_at":"2024-02-26T03:47:03Z","updated_at":"2024-02-28T00:16:08Z","closed_at":"2024-02-28T00:16:08Z","author_association":"CONTRIBUTOR","type":null,"active_lock_reason":null,"sub_issues_summary":{"total":0,"completed":0,"percent_completed":0},"issue_dependencies_summary":{"blocked_by":0,"total_blocked_by":0,"blocking":0,"total_blocking":0},"body":"Bevy has its own suite of errors available at https://bevyengine.org/learn/errors/#b0002 and https://github.com/bevyengine/bevy/tree/main/errors. However this info can be slightly difficult to search and find if you don't know exactly where to look. As an example just googling \"bevy errors\" doesnt return anything useful. Googling \"bevy errors b0001\" does return a link to the errors in Github but not to the main website. Furthermore requiring users to search for an error code on google is non optimal.\r\n\r\nAs a solution anytime an error is called explicitly it should include a link to that error so that users can access that additional information and help as easily as possible.\r\n\r\n### Old\r\n```\r\npanic!(\"error[B0003]: Could not insert a reflected component (of type {type_path}) for entity {entity:?} because it doesn't exist in this World.\");\r\n```\r\n\r\n### New\r\n```\r\npanic!(\"error[B0003] - https://bevyengine.org/learn/errors/#b0003: Could not insert a reflected component (of type {type_path}) for entity {entity:?} because it doesn't exist in this World.\");\r\n\r\n```","closed_by":{"login":"alice-i-cecile","id":3579909,"node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjM1Nzk5MDk=","avatar_url":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/3579909?v=4","gravatar_id":"","url":"ht